{
  "texts": [
    "For example, dialectometry is a research area that studies variations in dialects of a language [Goebl 1993] but is not included in the survey.",
    "TrendsTable 2 summarises the papers covered in this survey.",
    "We identify three trends in the past work:(1) Tasks in focus: Older research dealt with dialectal datasets primarily for dialect classification.Past work shows performance degradation when the text contains dialects of a language as compared to the predominant (i.e., standard) form.",
    "(2) Languages in focus: The papers reporting work on dialects of Arabic are significantly more than those for dialects of other languages.",
    "This has also been accelerated by research forums focusing on Arabic NLP."
  ]
}